{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"The world is changing"},{"time":2000,"text":"with really remarkable speed."},{"time":5000,"text":"If you look at the chart at the top here,"},{"time":7000,"text":"you'll see that in 2025,"},{"time":9000,"text":"these Goldman Sachs projections"},{"time":11000,"text":"suggest that the Chinese economy"},{"time":13000,"text":"will be almost the same size as the American economy."},{"time":16000,"text":"And if you look at the chart"},{"time":19000,"text":"for 2050,"},{"time":21000,"text":"it's projected that the Chinese economy"},{"time":24000,"text":"will be twice the size of the American economy,"},{"time":27000,"text":"and the Indian economy will be almost the same size"},{"time":29000,"text":"as the American economy."},{"time":32000,"text":"And we should bear in mind here"},{"time":34000,"text":"that these projections were drawn up"},{"time":36000,"text":"before the Western financial crisis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39000,"text":"A couple of weeks ago,"},{"time":41000,"text":"I was looking at the latest projection"},{"time":43000,"text":"by BNP Paribas"},{"time":45000,"text":"for when China"},{"time":48000,"text":"will have a larger economy"},{"time":50000,"text":"than the United States."},{"time":52000,"text":"Goldman Sachs projected 2027."},{"time":56000,"text":"The post-crisis projection"},{"time":59000,"text":"is 2020."},{"time":62000,"text":"That's just a decade away."},{"time":64000,"text":"China is going to change the world"},{"time":68000,"text":"in two fundamental respects."},{"time":71000,"text":"First of all,"},{"time":73000,"text":"it's a huge developing country"},{"time":75000,"text":"with a population of 1.3 billion people,"},{"time":79000,"text":"which has been growing for over 30 years"},{"time":82000,"text":"at around 10 percent a year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84000,"text":"And within a decade,"},{"time":86000,"text":"it will have the largest economy in the world."},{"time":90000,"text":"Never before in the modern era"},{"time":93000,"text":"has the largest economy in the world"},{"time":96000,"text":"been that of a developing country,"},{"time":98000,"text":"rather than a developed country."},{"time":102000,"text":"Secondly,"},{"time":104000,"text":"for the first time in the modern era,"},{"time":106000,"text":"the dominant country in the world --"},{"time":108000,"text":"which I think is what China will become --"},{"time":111000,"text":"will be not from the West"},{"time":114000,"text":"and from very, very different civilizational roots."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118000,"text":"Now, I know it's a widespread assumption in the West"},{"time":122000,"text":"that as countries modernize,"},{"time":125000,"text":"they also westernize."},{"time":127000,"text":"This is an illusion."},{"time":129000,"text":"It's an assumption that modernity"},{"time":131000,"text":"is a product simply of competition, markets and technology."},{"time":134000,"text":"It is not. It is also shaped equally"},{"time":136000,"text":"by history and culture."},{"time":138000,"text":"China is not like the West,"},{"time":141000,"text":"and it will not become like the West."},{"time":144000,"text":"It will remain in very fundamental respects"},{"time":146000,"text":"very different."},{"time":148000,"text":"Now the big question here is obviously,"},{"time":151000,"text":"how do we make sense of China?"},{"time":153000,"text":"How do we try to understand what China is?"},{"time":155000,"text":"And the problem we have in the West at the moment, by and large,"},{"time":158000,"text":"is that the conventional approach"},{"time":160000,"text":"is that we understand it really in Western terms,"},{"time":162000,"text":"using Western ideas."},{"time":165000,"text":"We can't."},{"time":167000,"text":"Now I want to offer you"},{"time":169000,"text":"three building blocks"},{"time":171000,"text":"for trying to understand what China is like,"},{"time":174000,"text":"just as a beginning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176000,"text":"The first is this:"},{"time":178000,"text":"that China is not really a nation-state."},{"time":181000,"text":"Okay, it's called itself a nation-state"},{"time":183000,"text":"for the last hundred years,"},{"time":185000,"text":"but everyone who knows anything about China"},{"time":187000,"text":"knows it's a lot older than this."},{"time":189000,"text":"This was what China looked like with the victory of the Qin Dynasty"},{"time":192000,"text":"in 221 B.C. at the end of the warring-state period --"},{"time":195000,"text":"the birth of modern China."},{"time":197000,"text":"And you can see it against the boundaries of modern China."},{"time":200000,"text":"Or immediately afterward, the Han Dynasty,"},{"time":202000,"text":"still 2,000 years ago."},{"time":204000,"text":"And you can see already it occupies"},{"time":206000,"text":"most of what we now know as Eastern China,"},{"time":208000,"text":"which is where the vast majority of Chinese lived then"},{"time":211000,"text":"and live now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":213000,"text":"Now what is extraordinary about this"},{"time":215000,"text":"is, what gives China its sense of being China,"},{"time":218000,"text":"what gives the Chinese"},{"time":221000,"text":"the sense of what it is to be Chinese,"},{"time":224000,"text":"comes not from the last hundred years,"},{"time":226000,"text":"not from the nation-state period,"},{"time":228000,"text":"which is what happened in the West,"},{"time":231000,"text":"but from the period, if you like,"},{"time":233000,"text":"of the civilization-state."},{"time":235000,"text":"I'm thinking here, for example,"},{"time":238000,"text":"of customs like ancestral worship,"},{"time":241000,"text":"of a very distinctive notion of the state,"},{"time":244000,"text":"likewise, a very distinctive notion of the family,"},{"time":247000,"text":"social relationships like guanxi,"},{"time":249000,"text":"Confucian values and so on."},{"time":251000,"text":"These are all things that come"},{"time":253000,"text":"from the period of the civilization-state."},{"time":256000,"text":"In other words, China, unlike the Western states and most countries in the world,"},{"time":259000,"text":"is shaped by its sense of civilization,"},{"time":262000,"text":"its existence as a civilization-state,"},{"time":264000,"text":"rather than as a nation-state."},{"time":266000,"text":"And there's one other thing to add to this, and that is this:"},{"time":269000,"text":"Of course we know China's big, huge,"},{"time":271000,"text":"demographically and geographically,"},{"time":274000,"text":"with a population of 1.3 billion people."},{"time":277000,"text":"What we often aren't really aware of"},{"time":280000,"text":"is the fact"},{"time":282000,"text":"that China is extremely diverse"},{"time":284000,"text":"and very pluralistic,"},{"time":286000,"text":"and in many ways very decentralized."},{"time":288000,"text":"You can't run a place on this scale simply from Beijing,"},{"time":291000,"text":"even though we think this to be the case."},{"time":294000,"text":"It's never been the case."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298000,"text":"So this is China, a civilization-state,"},{"time":300000,"text":"rather than a nation-state."},{"time":302000,"text":"And what does it mean?"},{"time":304000,"text":"Well, I think it has all sorts of profound implications."},{"time":306000,"text":"I'll give you two quick ones."},{"time":308000,"text":"The first is that"},{"time":310000,"text":"the most important political value for the Chinese"},{"time":314000,"text":"is unity,"},{"time":316000,"text":"is the maintenance"},{"time":318000,"text":"of Chinese civilization."},{"time":320000,"text":"You know, 2,000 years ago, Europe:"},{"time":323000,"text":"breakdown -- the fragmentation of the Holy Roman Empire."},{"time":326000,"text":"It divided, and it's remained divided ever since."},{"time":329000,"text":"China, over the same time period,"},{"time":331000,"text":"went in exactly the opposite direction,"},{"time":333000,"text":"very painfully holding this huge civilization,"},{"time":336000,"text":"civilization-state, together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":339000,"text":"The second"},{"time":341000,"text":"is maybe more prosaic,"},{"time":343000,"text":"which is Hong Kong."},{"time":345000,"text":"Do you remember the handover of Hong Kong"},{"time":348000,"text":"by Britain to China in 1997?"},{"time":350000,"text":"You may remember"},{"time":352000,"text":"what the Chinese constitutional proposition was."},{"time":354000,"text":"One country, two systems."},{"time":356000,"text":"And I'll lay a wager"},{"time":358000,"text":"that barely anyone in the West believed them."},{"time":360000,"text":"\"Window dressing."},{"time":362000,"text":"When China gets its hands on Hong Kong,"},{"time":364000,"text":"that won't be the case.\""},{"time":366000,"text":"Thirteen years on,"},{"time":368000,"text":"the political and legal system in Hong Kong"},{"time":370000,"text":"is as different now as it was in 1997."},{"time":373000,"text":"We were wrong. Why were we wrong?"},{"time":376000,"text":"We were wrong because we thought, naturally enough,"},{"time":379000,"text":"in nation-state ways."},{"time":381000,"text":"Think of German unification, 1990."},{"time":383000,"text":"What happened?"},{"time":385000,"text":"Well, basically the East was swallowed by the West."},{"time":387000,"text":"One nation, one system."},{"time":389000,"text":"That is the nation-state mentality."},{"time":392000,"text":"But you can't run a country like China,"},{"time":395000,"text":"a civilization-state,"},{"time":397000,"text":"on the basis of one civilization, one system."},{"time":400000,"text":"It doesn't work."},{"time":402000,"text":"So actually the response of China"},{"time":405000,"text":"to the question of Hong Kong --"},{"time":407000,"text":"as it will be to the question of Taiwan --"},{"time":409000,"text":"was a natural response:"},{"time":411000,"text":"one civilization, many systems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":414000,"text":"Let me offer you another building block"},{"time":416000,"text":"to try and understand China --"},{"time":418000,"text":"maybe not sort of a comfortable one."},{"time":421000,"text":"The Chinese have a very, very different"},{"time":423000,"text":"conception of race"},{"time":425000,"text":"to most other countries."},{"time":428000,"text":"Do you know,"},{"time":430000,"text":"of the 1.3 billion Chinese,"},{"time":433000,"text":"over 90 percent of them"},{"time":435000,"text":"think they belong to the same race,"},{"time":438000,"text":"the Han?"},{"time":440000,"text":"Now, this is completely different"},{"time":442000,"text":"from the world's [other] most populous countries."},{"time":445000,"text":"India, the United States,"},{"time":447000,"text":"Indonesia, Brazil --"},{"time":450000,"text":"all of them are multiracial."},{"time":453000,"text":"The Chinese don't feel like that."},{"time":456000,"text":"China is only multiracial"},{"time":458000,"text":"really at the margins."},{"time":461000,"text":"So the question is, why?"},{"time":463000,"text":"Well the reason, I think, essentially"},{"time":465000,"text":"is, again, back to the civilization-state."},{"time":468000,"text":"A history of at least 2,000 years,"},{"time":471000,"text":"a history of conquest, occupation,"},{"time":473000,"text":"absorption, assimilation and so on,"},{"time":475000,"text":"led to the process by which,"},{"time":477000,"text":"over time, this notion of the Han emerged --"},{"time":480000,"text":"of course, nurtured"},{"time":482000,"text":"by a growing and very powerful sense"},{"time":485000,"text":"of cultural identity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":488000,"text":"Now the great advantage of this historical experience"},{"time":491000,"text":"has been that, without the Han,"},{"time":495000,"text":"China could never have held together."},{"time":497000,"text":"The Han identity has been the cement"},{"time":500000,"text":"which has held this country together."},{"time":503000,"text":"The great disadvantage of it"},{"time":505000,"text":"is that the Han have a very weak conception"},{"time":507000,"text":"of cultural difference."},{"time":509000,"text":"They really believe"},{"time":512000,"text":"in their own superiority,"},{"time":514000,"text":"and they are disrespectful"},{"time":516000,"text":"of those who are not."},{"time":518000,"text":"Hence their attitude, for example,"},{"time":520000,"text":"to the Uyghurs and to the Tibetans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":524000,"text":"Or let me give you my third building block,"},{"time":526000,"text":"the Chinese state."},{"time":528000,"text":"Now the relationship"},{"time":530000,"text":"between the state and society in China"},{"time":533000,"text":"is very different from that in the West."},{"time":537000,"text":"Now we in the West"},{"time":539000,"text":"overwhelmingly seem to think -- in these days at least --"},{"time":541000,"text":"that the authority and legitimacy of the state"},{"time":545000,"text":"is a function of democracy."},{"time":548000,"text":"The problem with this proposition"},{"time":550000,"text":"is that the Chinese state"},{"time":554000,"text":"enjoys more legitimacy"},{"time":556000,"text":"and more authority"},{"time":558000,"text":"amongst the Chinese"},{"time":561000,"text":"than is true"},{"time":563000,"text":"with any Western state."},{"time":567000,"text":"And the reason for this"},{"time":569000,"text":"is because --"},{"time":571000,"text":"well, there are two reasons, I think."},{"time":573000,"text":"And it's obviously got nothing to do with democracy,"},{"time":575000,"text":"because in our terms the Chinese certainly don't have a democracy."},{"time":578000,"text":"And the reason for this is,"},{"time":580000,"text":"firstly, because the state in China"},{"time":583000,"text":"is given a very special --"},{"time":586000,"text":"it enjoys a very special significance"},{"time":588000,"text":"as the representative,"},{"time":590000,"text":"the embodiment and the guardian"},{"time":593000,"text":"of Chinese civilization,"},{"time":595000,"text":"of the civilization-state."},{"time":598000,"text":"This is as close as China gets"},{"time":600000,"text":"to a kind of spiritual role."}]},{"cues":[{"time":604000,"text":"And the second reason is because,"},{"time":606000,"text":"whereas in Europe"},{"time":608000,"text":"and North America,"},{"time":610000,"text":"the state's power is continuously challenged --"},{"time":613000,"text":"I mean in the European tradition,"},{"time":615000,"text":"historically against the church,"},{"time":617000,"text":"against other sectors of the aristocracy,"},{"time":619000,"text":"against merchants and so on --"},{"time":621000,"text":"for 1,000 years,"},{"time":623000,"text":"the power of the Chinese state"},{"time":625000,"text":"has not been challenged."},{"time":627000,"text":"It's had no serious rivals."},{"time":631000,"text":"So you can see"},{"time":633000,"text":"that the way in which power has been constructed in China"},{"time":637000,"text":"is very different from our experience"},{"time":639000,"text":"in Western history."},{"time":642000,"text":"The result, by the way,"},{"time":644000,"text":"is that the Chinese have a very different view of the state."},{"time":649000,"text":"Whereas we tend to view it as an intruder,"},{"time":652000,"text":"a stranger,"},{"time":655000,"text":"certainly an organ"},{"time":657000,"text":"whose powers need to be limited"},{"time":660000,"text":"or defined and constrained,"},{"time":662000,"text":"the Chinese don't see the state like that at all."},{"time":664000,"text":"The Chinese view the state"},{"time":667000,"text":"as an intimate -- not just as an intimate actually,"},{"time":670000,"text":"as a member of the family --"},{"time":672000,"text":"not just in fact as a member of the family,"},{"time":674000,"text":"but as the head of the family,"},{"time":676000,"text":"the patriarch of the family."},{"time":678000,"text":"This is the Chinese view of the state --"},{"time":681000,"text":"very, very different to ours."},{"time":683000,"text":"It's embedded in society in a different kind of way"},{"time":686000,"text":"to what is the case"},{"time":688000,"text":"in the West."}]},{"cues":[{"time":690000,"text":"And I would suggest to you that actually what we are dealing with here,"},{"time":693000,"text":"in the Chinese context,"},{"time":696000,"text":"is a new kind of paradigm,"},{"time":698000,"text":"which is different from anything"},{"time":700000,"text":"we've had to think about in the past."},{"time":704000,"text":"Know that China believes in the market and the state."},{"time":707000,"text":"I mean, Adam Smith,"},{"time":709000,"text":"already writing in the late 18th century, said,"},{"time":712000,"text":"\"The Chinese market is larger and more developed"},{"time":714000,"text":"and more sophisticated"},{"time":716000,"text":"than anything in Europe.\""},{"time":718000,"text":"And, apart from the Mao period,"},{"time":720000,"text":"that has remained more or less the case ever since."},{"time":722000,"text":"But this is combined"},{"time":724000,"text":"with an extremely strong and ubiquitous state."},{"time":728000,"text":"The state is everywhere in China."},{"time":730000,"text":"I mean, it's leading firms --"},{"time":732000,"text":"many of them are still publicly owned."},{"time":735000,"text":"Private firms, however large they are, like Lenovo,"},{"time":738000,"text":"depend in many ways on state patronage."},{"time":740000,"text":"Targets for the economy and so on"},{"time":742000,"text":"are set by the state."},{"time":744000,"text":"And the state, of course, its authority flows into lots of other areas --"},{"time":746000,"text":"as we are familiar with --"},{"time":748000,"text":"with something like the one-child policy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":750000,"text":"Moreover, this is a very old state tradition,"},{"time":753000,"text":"a very old tradition of statecraft."},{"time":755000,"text":"I mean, if you want an illustration of this,"},{"time":758000,"text":"the Great Wall is one."},{"time":760000,"text":"But this is another, this is the Grand Canal,"},{"time":762000,"text":"which was constructed in the first instance"},{"time":764000,"text":"in the fifth century B.C."},{"time":766000,"text":"and was finally completed"},{"time":768000,"text":"in the seventh century A.D."},{"time":770000,"text":"It went for 1,114 miles,"},{"time":774000,"text":"linking Beijing"},{"time":776000,"text":"with Hangzhou and Shanghai."},{"time":779000,"text":"So there's a long history"},{"time":781000,"text":"of extraordinary state infrastructural projects"},{"time":784000,"text":"in China,"},{"time":786000,"text":"which I suppose helps us to explain what we see today,"},{"time":789000,"text":"which is something like the Three Gorges Dam"},{"time":791000,"text":"and many other expressions"},{"time":793000,"text":"of state competence"},{"time":795000,"text":"within China."},{"time":797000,"text":"So there we have three building blocks"},{"time":800000,"text":"for trying to understand the difference that is China --"},{"time":803000,"text":"the civilization-state,"},{"time":806000,"text":"the notion of race"},{"time":808000,"text":"and the nature of the state"},{"time":810000,"text":"and its relationship to society."}]},{"cues":[{"time":813000,"text":"And yet we still insist, by and large,"},{"time":816000,"text":"in thinking that we can understand China"},{"time":820000,"text":"by simply drawing on Western experience,"},{"time":823000,"text":"looking at it through Western eyes,"},{"time":826000,"text":"using Western concepts."},{"time":828000,"text":"If you want to know why"},{"time":830000,"text":"we unerringly seem to get China wrong --"},{"time":833000,"text":"our predictions about what's going to happen to China are incorrect --"},{"time":836000,"text":"this is the reason."},{"time":840000,"text":"Unfortunately, I think,"},{"time":842000,"text":"I have to say that I think"},{"time":845000,"text":"attitude towards China"},{"time":847000,"text":"is that of a kind of little Westerner mentality."},{"time":850000,"text":"It's kind of arrogant."},{"time":852000,"text":"It's arrogant in the sense"},{"time":854000,"text":"that we think that we are best,"},{"time":856000,"text":"and therefore we have the universal measure."},{"time":860000,"text":"And secondly, it's ignorant."},{"time":862000,"text":"We refuse to really address"},{"time":865000,"text":"the issue of difference."},{"time":867000,"text":"You know, there's a very interesting passage"},{"time":869000,"text":"in a book by Paul Cohen, the American historian."},{"time":872000,"text":"And Paul Cohen argues"},{"time":875000,"text":"that the West thinks of itself"},{"time":879000,"text":"as probably the most cosmopolitan"},{"time":881000,"text":"of all cultures."},{"time":883000,"text":"But it's not."},{"time":885000,"text":"In many ways,"},{"time":887000,"text":"it's the most parochial,"},{"time":889000,"text":"because for 200 years,"},{"time":892000,"text":"the West has been so dominant in the world"},{"time":895000,"text":"that it's not really needed"},{"time":897000,"text":"to understand other cultures,"},{"time":900000,"text":"other civilizations."},{"time":902000,"text":"Because, at the end of the day,"},{"time":904000,"text":"it could, if necessary by force,"},{"time":907000,"text":"get its own way."},{"time":909000,"text":"Whereas those cultures --"},{"time":911000,"text":"virtually the rest of the world, in fact,"},{"time":914000,"text":"which have been in a far weaker position, vis-a-vis the West --"},{"time":917000,"text":"have been thereby forced to understand the West,"},{"time":920000,"text":"because of the West's presence in those societies."},{"time":923000,"text":"And therefore, they are, as a result,"},{"time":926000,"text":"more cosmopolitan in many ways than the West."}]},{"cues":[{"time":929000,"text":"I mean, take the question of East Asia."},{"time":931000,"text":"East Asia: Japan, Korea, China, etc. --"},{"time":934000,"text":"a third of the world's population lives there."},{"time":936000,"text":"Now the largest economic region in the world."},{"time":938000,"text":"And I'll tell you now,"},{"time":940000,"text":"that East Asianers, people from East Asia,"},{"time":942000,"text":"are far more knowledgeable"},{"time":944000,"text":"about the West"},{"time":946000,"text":"than the West is about East Asia."},{"time":950000,"text":"Now this point is very germane, I'm afraid,"},{"time":953000,"text":"to the present."},{"time":955000,"text":"Because what's happening? Back to that chart at the beginning,"},{"time":958000,"text":"the Goldman Sachs chart."},{"time":960000,"text":"What is happening"},{"time":962000,"text":"is that, very rapidly in historical terms,"},{"time":965000,"text":"the world is being driven"},{"time":968000,"text":"and shaped,"},{"time":970000,"text":"not by the old developed countries,"},{"time":972000,"text":"but by the developing world."},{"time":974000,"text":"We've seen this"},{"time":976000,"text":"in terms of the G20"},{"time":978000,"text":"usurping very rapidly the position of the G7,"},{"time":981000,"text":"or the G8."},{"time":985000,"text":"And there are two consequences of this."},{"time":988000,"text":"First, the West"},{"time":990000,"text":"is rapidly losing"},{"time":992000,"text":"its influence in the world."},{"time":994000,"text":"There was a dramatic illustration of this actually a year ago --"},{"time":997000,"text":"Copenhagen, climate change conference."},{"time":999000,"text":"Europe was not at the final negotiating table."},{"time":1001000,"text":"When did that last happen?"},{"time":1003000,"text":"I would wager it was probably about 200 years ago."},{"time":1006000,"text":"And that is what is going to happen in the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1009000,"text":"And the second implication"},{"time":1011000,"text":"is that the world will inevitably, as a consequence,"},{"time":1014000,"text":"become increasingly unfamiliar to us,"},{"time":1018000,"text":"because it'll be shaped by cultures and experiences and histories"},{"time":1021000,"text":"that we are not really familiar with,"},{"time":1024000,"text":"or conversant with."},{"time":1026000,"text":"And at last, I'm afraid -- take Europe;"},{"time":1028000,"text":"America is slightly different --"},{"time":1030000,"text":"but Europeans by and large, I have to say,"},{"time":1033000,"text":"are ignorant,"},{"time":1036000,"text":"are unaware"},{"time":1038000,"text":"about the way the world is changing."},{"time":1041000,"text":"Some people -- I've got an English friend in China,"},{"time":1044000,"text":"and he said, \"The continent is sleepwalking into oblivion.\""},{"time":1049000,"text":"Well, maybe that's true,"},{"time":1051000,"text":"maybe that's an exaggeration."},{"time":1053000,"text":"But there's another problem which goes along with this --"},{"time":1056000,"text":"that Europe is increasingly out of touch with the world --"},{"time":1059000,"text":"and that is a sort of"},{"time":1062000,"text":"loss of a sense of the future."},{"time":1064000,"text":"I mean, Europe once, of course, once commanded the future"},{"time":1067000,"text":"in its confidence."},{"time":1069000,"text":"Take the 19th century, for example."},{"time":1072000,"text":"But this, alas, is no longer true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1075000,"text":"If you want to feel the future, if you want to taste the future,"},{"time":1078000,"text":"try China -- there's old Confucius."},{"time":1081000,"text":"This is a railway station"},{"time":1083000,"text":"the likes of which you've never seen before."},{"time":1085000,"text":"It doesn't even look like a railway station."},{"time":1087000,"text":"This is the new [Wuhan] railway station"},{"time":1089000,"text":"for the high-speed trains."},{"time":1091000,"text":"China already has a bigger network"},{"time":1093000,"text":"than any other country in the world"},{"time":1095000,"text":"and will soon have more than all the rest of the world put together."},{"time":1099000,"text":"Or take this: now this is an idea,"},{"time":1101000,"text":"but it's an idea to be tried out shortly"},{"time":1104000,"text":"in a suburb of Beijing."},{"time":1106000,"text":"Here you have a megabus,"},{"time":1109000,"text":"on the upper deck carries about 2,000 people."},{"time":1112000,"text":"It travels on rails"},{"time":1114000,"text":"down a suburban road,"},{"time":1116000,"text":"and the cars travel underneath it."},{"time":1119000,"text":"And it does speeds of up to about 100 miles an hour."},{"time":1122000,"text":"Now this is the way things are going to move,"},{"time":1125000,"text":"because China has a very specific problem,"},{"time":1127000,"text":"which is different from Europe"},{"time":1129000,"text":"and different from the United States:"},{"time":1131000,"text":"China has huge numbers of people and no space."},{"time":1134000,"text":"So this is a solution to a situation"},{"time":1136000,"text":"where China's going to have"},{"time":1138000,"text":"many, many, many cities"},{"time":1140000,"text":"over 20 million people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1142000,"text":"Okay, so how would I like to finish?"},{"time":1145000,"text":"Well, what should our attitude be"},{"time":1148000,"text":"towards this world"},{"time":1151000,"text":"that we see"},{"time":1153000,"text":"very rapidly developing"},{"time":1155000,"text":"before us?"},{"time":1158000,"text":"I think there will be good things about it and there will be bad things about it."},{"time":1161000,"text":"But I want to argue, above all,"},{"time":1163000,"text":"a big-picture positive for this world."},{"time":1168000,"text":"For 200 years,"},{"time":1170000,"text":"the world was essentially governed"},{"time":1176000,"text":"by a fragment of the human population."},{"time":1180000,"text":"That's what Europe and North America represented."},{"time":1184000,"text":"The arrival of countries"},{"time":1186000,"text":"like China and India --"},{"time":1188000,"text":"between them 38 percent of the world's population --"},{"time":1190000,"text":"and others like Indonesia and Brazil and so on,"},{"time":1196000,"text":"represent the most important single act"},{"time":1199000,"text":"of democratization"},{"time":1201000,"text":"in the last 200 years."},{"time":1203000,"text":"Civilizations and cultures,"},{"time":1205000,"text":"which had been ignored, which had no voice,"},{"time":1208000,"text":"which were not listened to, which were not known about,"},{"time":1210000,"text":"will have a different sort"},{"time":1212000,"text":"of representation in this world."},{"time":1215000,"text":"As humanists, we must welcome, surely,"},{"time":1217000,"text":"this transformation,"},{"time":1219000,"text":"and we will have to learn"},{"time":1221000,"text":"about these civilizations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1223000,"text":"This big ship here"},{"time":1226000,"text":"was the one sailed in by Zheng He"},{"time":1228000,"text":"in the early 15th century"},{"time":1230000,"text":"on his great voyages"},{"time":1232000,"text":"around the South China Sea, the East China Sea"},{"time":1235000,"text":"and across the Indian Ocean to East Africa."},{"time":1238000,"text":"The little boat in front of it"},{"time":1242000,"text":"was the one in which, 80 years later,"},{"time":1244000,"text":"Christopher Columbus crossed the Atlantic."},{"time":1247000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1249000,"text":"Or, look carefully"},{"time":1251000,"text":"at this silk scroll"},{"time":1253000,"text":"made by ZhuZhou"},{"time":1256000,"text":"in 1368."},{"time":1259000,"text":"I think they're playing golf."},{"time":1261000,"text":"Christ, the Chinese even invented golf."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1264000,"text":"Welcome to the future. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1267000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}